4eb7-470a-bced-4c82dc594e3a"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"be192aa71974e1dac5d4cf693a1e86ab3473ac90f1deca8324b80096026d11fd","event_uuid":"6a060df7-57a1-408d-b4f1-49b8bd1dd6a1","position":{"commit_sha":"3ffd45b8db300c84837ddf8158a1be89c1128744","position":"1784439323127050613-6a060df7-57a1-408d-b4f1-49b8bd1dd6a1"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"0598b281-0286-4b2c-891c-cc5b4c94ba24","comments":[],"created_at":1784143936423895001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"d1e5caee-940e-4085-97d9-128d8114ccef","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"5342-568c-b881-4b2a"},{"link_uuid":"3a6380d0-998d-43ec-bb7d-3cbb5d31e26c","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"a880-b7e1-dc3e-407c"},{"link_uuid":"16dd930b-49f7-4cca-803c-72447d03939e","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"7d91-55fc-e07c-4101"},{"link_uuid":"0be49e4c-f57e-4a5d-8d23-66027be2458a","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"59b7-69b6-e763-4a83"}],"description":"## Why\nR1's asserted-capability probe (plan-review) flags a plan that CLAIMS a capability an existing module lacks. R5 adds the Pass-2 verification counterpart in the SHARED kernel: a dedicated `asserted_capability_confirmed` sub-answer so the verifier can confirm/refute a capability-gap finding on the evidence instead of overloading `no_viable_alternative_explanation`. The kernel vocabulary is SHARED with code-review (`src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py:31 GRADED_BINARY`), so this is the epic's highest-blast-radius change and sits behind the strictest gates (E5 byte-identical replay + E6 self-consistency κ=0.874).\n\n## What\nAdd `asserted_capability_confirmed` to the shared kernel `GRADED_BINARY` (decide.py:31) as an **na-DEFAULT** graded VALIDITY sub-answer (registered in `verify_models._BINARY_NA_DEFAULT`), with the SAME `yes=finding-holds` polarity as every other graded sub-answer (`validity()`, decide.py:56 — yes=1.0, insufficient=0.5, no=0.0):\n- `yes` = the review CONFIRMS the asserted gap (the capability really is absent/unwired) — the finding HOLDS, validity retained;\n- `no` = the capability is in fact delivered/exercised, REFUTING the finding — validity drops so a FALSE non-delivery claim is dropped;\n- `na` (default) everywhere OUTSIDE the G6/E4/T3 asserted-capability cohort → abstains from the graded mean.\nBecause `_build_binary` (verify_models.py) is shared, BOTH the plan-review and code-review Binary models inherit it. Landed directly in the packaged kernel (no config flag), on E5 + E6 pass.\n\n## Design reconciliation (resolves plan-review G6 + T8 on this ticket)\n- **Validity axis, not impact promotion — deliberate.** `docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md:197` sketches feeding a `no` into `divergent_implementation` to LIFT priority. That is the PLAN-review R1 direction (promote a plan's forward claim that later forces redesign). R5 is the CODE-review verification counterpart: at code-review time the capability's presence is DIRECTLY checkable against the diff, so the honest, non-destabilising move is to CONFIRM/REFUTE the finding on the validity axis (weeding false non-delivery claims), NOT to inflate priority. A genuine confirmed gap is surfaced by the finding's OWN impact axes; R5 only prevents a false capability-claim from riding on unearned validity. This is why a `no` correctly drives toward dropped — the capability was delivered, so the non-delivery finding is a false positive.\n- **No cross-field coupling.** R5 introduces NO rule that co-populates `divergent_implementation` (a `PlanSeverityAttrs` severity axis) from this binary. The research-doc coupling is explicitly NOT replicated; the sub-answer's only effect is through `validity()`. Recorded in `docs/review-kernel.md`.\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py` — one entry in `GRADED_BINARY`.\n- `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/verify_models.py` — `_BINARY_DESC` + `_BINARY_NA_DEFAULT` entry. (NEW module: the Pass-2 model builders were extracted from `verify.py` along the existing call-graph seam to hold the LOCKED 800-LOC hard cap — `verify.py` sat at exactly 800; names re-exported from `verify`, no import site changed.)\n- `tests/unit/test_r5_asserted_capability.py` — invariance + registration + polarity tests.\n- `docs/review-kernel.md` — na-default sub-answer + validity-axis-vs-research reconciliation + no-bump note.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Gate-row evidence committed before landing: E5 byte-identical replay artifact (`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/e5_nonregression_diff.json` — empty decision/priority/validity diff over the 161-row code-review corpus, `na` outside G6/E4/T3) AND E6 Exp A κ≥0.6 (recorded κ=0.874 PASS).\n- [ ] `asserted_capability_confirmed` added to the shared `GRADED_BINARY` as an na-default graded sub-answer with `yes=finding-holds` polarity; both plan-review and code-review Binary models default it to `na`. Pinned by `tests/unit/test_r5_asserted_capability.py` (`test_field_registered_and_na_default`, `test_cohort_answer_contributes_to_validity`).\n- [ ] Code-review behaviour pinned UNCHANGED by a regression test (the invariance property in `test_r5_asserted_capability.py` + the E5 replay driver): validity/decision byte-identical whether the field is absent or `na`.\n- [ ] IMPACT_MODEL_VERSION deliberately NOT bumped — grounded correction of the stub AC: the field is a validity axis touching neither `impact_code` nor `impact_plan` SHAPE (`code_review/sidecar.py:34` bumps only on impact_code shape change), and the byte-identical property (E5) requires sidecars stay un-segmented. Rationale in `docs/review-kernel.md` + the E5 writeup. No cross-field coupling to `divergent_implementation` (resolves G6/T8).\n- [ ] Landed directly in the packaged kernel (no config flag) through Gerrit (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1); module-size hard-800 respected; `docs/review-kernel.md` updated.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/","reason":"verification vocabulary + decide math"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py","reason":"version bump + persistence"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","5342-568c-b881-4b2a"],["depends_on","7d91-55fc-e07c-4101"],["depends_on","a880-b7e1-dc3e-407c"],["parent","6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9"],["relates_to","59b7-69b6-e763-4a83"]],"parent_id":"6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9","parent_status_uuid":"e596f1ae-baca-46c1-8051-ab8c0dd6014a","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"ea39-c2d1-e26a-4ee6","ticket_type":"story","title":"R5: asserted_capability_confirmed kernel sub-answer (gated on E5+E6, version bump)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["e310bd88-7730-4882-8886-9df0bf003159","d1e5caee-940e-4085-97d9-128d8114ccef","3a6380d0-998d-43ec-bb7d-3cbb5d31e26c","16dd930b-49f7-4cca-803c-72447d03939e","75e7d57e-51db-466f-ba1c-ba64eeae2c54","0be49e4c-f57e-4a5d-8d23-66027be2458a","8abe0c59-6199-4d1a-8d99-b25d3e2ce9b2","643f8520-1cbc-409f-8fc2-658cecb889b7","a051c1b5-9e7d-40db-9c75-4d758bc6d25f","e596f1ae-baca-46c1-8051-ab8c0dd6014a","aec86c0b-4eb7-470a-bced-4c82dc594e3a","6a060df7-57a1-408d-b4f1-49b8bd1dd6a1"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784439323127050614,"uuid":"